<subSubSection id="16F00DFCFFD13348FF6CFAC6733FF947" pageId="9" pageNumber="204" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5E555E77FFD13348FF6CFAC6733FF947" blockId="9.[176,1235,1284,1823]" pageId="9" pageNumber="204">
D i a g n o s i s. 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD13348FE05FAC67037FA86" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1934" box="[396,516,1284,1311]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Prohypotyphla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scalaris">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD13348FE05FAC673ACFA86" box="[396,415,1284,1310]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="204">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD13348FE25FAC67037FA86" box="[428,516,1284,1310]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="204">scalaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a species superficially similar to 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD13348FC28FAC67609FA86" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1843" box="[929,1082,1284,1311]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD13348FC28FAC67187FA86" box="[929,948,1284,1310]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="204">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD13348FC48FAC67609FA86" box="[961,1082,1284,1310]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="204">ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its almost uniformly yellowishbody often with reddish-yellow lyrate pattern on scutum and whitish scutellum, hyaline wings, medium-size (wing length 6.5–8.1 mm), and only one pair of ocellar and one pair of postocellar setae present, with pedicel moderately elongate, shorter than flagellomere 1 (the latter parallel-sided, twice as long as wide and apically blunt), lacking outer vertical setae, mid coxae with 2 setae laterally and short setulae medioventrally, short setulose hind coxae, femora not thickened, with long basal and subbasal ventral setae, fore femur without long dorsal setae, mid and hind femora with short and thin apicoventral setae, scutellum short setulose with 4 scutellar setae, wide abdomen, differing from other 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD13348FDAEF9E670F1F9A6" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1843" box="[551,706,1572,1598]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD13348FDAEF9E670F1F9A6" box="[551,706,1572,1598]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="204">Campylocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the wide conical oviscape without setose swellings but with a ventral incision (lateral view). It is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD13348FBC2F9867332F9E7" authority="Becker" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unicolor">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD13348FBC2F98676E0F9C6" box="[1099,1235,1604,1630]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="204">C. unicolor</emphasis>
Becker
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="99EA25F4FFD13348FEB7F9A673D4F9E6" authorityName="Korneyev" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Aczel" baseAuthorityYear="1958" box="[318,487,1636,1662]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Campylocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="204" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hyalipennis">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD13348FEB7F9A673D4F9E6" box="[318,487,1636,1662]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="204">C. hyalipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see discussion above), differing from the second by the blunt flagellomere 1, slightly darker mesonotum and somewhat wider aculeus (
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFD13348FB98F946767DF907" box="[1041,1102,1668,1695]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[170,203,1230,1252]" captionTargetBox="[292,1089,179,1194]" captionTargetId="figure-11@8.[287,1092,174,1227]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 8. Campylocera scalaris holotype ♀ (NHMW): 1 — habitus, lateral view; 2 —wing; 3 — head, left (arrow indicates enlarged setae); 4 —head, dorsal view; 5 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 6 — fore leg, posterior view; 7 — mid leg, anterior; 8 — hind leg, anterior view; 9 — oviscape, dorsal and left view; 10 — labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453710/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="204">fig. 8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C6D142F2FFD13348FBD0F9467654F906" box="[1113,1127,1668,1694]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[168,201,1786,1808]" captionTargetBox="[292,1119,675,1772]" captionTargetId="figure-200@4.[272,1119,667,1775]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 3. Campylocera ferruginea, non-type Ơ (1–6) and ♀ (7–11) (Nigeria, USNM): 1–2 — genitalia, right and ventral view; 3 — outer and inner surstyli, ventral view; 4–6 — phallus glans at different angles; 7 — oviscape apex; 8 — aculeus; 9 — vagina and ventral receptacle; 10 — medioventral lobe; 11 — spermathecae (2 of 3)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453694/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="204">
<emphasis id="6C9E8265FFD13348FBD0F9467654F906" box="[1113,1127,1668,1694]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="204">3</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
), but the ranges of variability of these characters need additional studies to see if they are separate species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="16F00DFCFFD13348FF6CF9267115F887" pageId="9" pageNumber="204" type="discussion">
